titles.title: To provide for the liquidation or reliquidation of certain entries.

action.text: Referred to the House Committee on Ways and Means.
Referred to the Subcommittee on Trade.

committee.name: House Committee on Ways and Means

bill.summary: 3/17/1998--Introduced. Requires the U.S. Customs Service to liquidate or reliquidate specified entries in accordance with the final decision of the International Trade Administration of the Department of Commerce for shipments entered between October 1, 1984, and December 14, 1987.
